at the same time the court also agreed to study the refund issue 
in a case from florida involving taxes on alcoholic beverages the 
justices said they will hear an appeal by mckesson corp a 
wholesale liquor distributor seeking a refund for taxes paid under 
a state levy that allegedly favored instate companies 
in the arkansas case the truck tax was declared unconstitutional 
last march by the state supreme court 
that court based its ruling on a us supreme court decision in 
june 1987 that struck down a similar tax in pennsylvania on grounds 
it discriminated unlawfully against interstate truckers 
the arkansas court ordered state officials to refund to 
interstate truckers 49 million that had been held in a special 
escrow fund created in august 1987 
but the state court said the truckers were not entitled to 
additional refunds on taxes the state collected but had not placed 
in the separate fund 
the state court said it would be unfair to apply the 1987 us 
supreme court ruling retroactively and award the interstate truckers 
the additional refunds 
the equities favor disallowing refund of the tax money already 
paid into the state treasury the state court said 
the us supreme court in 1987 struck down a socalled flat tax 
that pennsylvania had imposed on all truck companies that used its 
highways the justices said the tax favored pennsylvania companies 
because they paid the same amount of money as interstate haulers 
even though the trucks owned by interstate companies traveled far 
fewer miles on pennsylvania highways 
the american trucking association which successfully challenged 
the pennsylvania tax noted that the arkansas legislature repealed 
that states flat tax in october 1987 and replaced it with one that 
imposed a rate of 25 cents per mile on all users of arkansas 
highways 
but the new law allowed arkansas officials to collect the 
invalidated tax for another year 
the trucking association did not specify the size of the 
additional refunds it sought for its members but the invalidated 
arkansas tax produced some 23 million in annual revenue 
the case are mckesson corp vs division of alcoholic beverages 
and american truck associations vs smith 88325 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

