three light earthquakes shook 
northern california monday but there were no reports of damage or 
injuries the us geological service said 
the three quakes appeared to be centered on the san andreas 
fault said pat jorgenson 
the first quake struck at 1058 am and registered 24 on the 
richter scale said jorgenson the second was at 1121 with a 30 
magnitude and the final one hit at 1152 am registering 275 
all three were in a location about 30 miles south of san 
francisco 
the openended richter scale is a measure of the energy released 
by an earthquake 
a quake of 35 can cause slight damage in populated areas while 
a quake of 60 can cause severe damage 
