<TEXT>
commodore international ltd the 
resurgent maker of microcomputers on monday unveiled three new 
models aimed at business users including two additions to its amiga 
line intended to compete with apple computer incs macintosh 
the amiga 2500 and the amiga 2000hd are the first additions to 
the line since two machines one intended primarily for home use and 
another for business were unveiled in april 1987 
the amiga ranks fourth in us sales among computers with 32bit 
microprocessors behind the macintosh international business 
machines corps personal system2 model 70 and compaq computer 
corps deskpro 386 according to market researcher ims america ltd 
especially with apples introduction of the mac ii and iix 
they needed to get the new amigas out because amiga was the hardware 
leader three years ago said rhett anderson associate editor of 
compute gazette a magazine targeted at commodore users and 
published in greensboro nc 
some of their thinking might be if they get these out before 
christmas they consumers might hear the word amiga and some might 
take 500s last years lowcost home computer model home he said 
the new amigas offer twice the capacity of the earlier models and 
a faster microprocessor 
the 2000hd comes with software loaded on a hard disk so the 
machine is ready to use right out of the box said spokesman gary 
fishman 
