<TEXT>
comdex the annual barometer of the economic 
health of the computer industry opened monday with the promoter of 
the event pronouncing the patient in good condition 
more than 100000 people are expected to attend this years show 
which runs through friday demands for exhibit space are up 14 
percent over a year ago 
obviously the computer industry is alive and well said 
sheldon adelson chairman of the interface group the producer of 
the fiveday event 
more than 1700 companies are exhibiting their computer wares at 
this years show with displays covering 175 million square feet in 
eight locations 
the weeks activities range from parties introducing new products 
to seminars on a host of topics from industry trends to battling 
computer viruses 
adelson in an interview sunday said he expected this 10th 
anniversary show to break all records in terms of attendance 
display space foreign companies exhibiting their wares and media in 
attendance 
the booming attendance is a good sign for the computer industry 
adelson said 
comdex reflects the health of the computer industry adelson 
said how the show goes so goes the industry and vice versa the 
turnout at this years show demonstrates that the industry is alive 
and well 
adelson said personal computers pcs and laptop computers are 
expected to be the big drawing card again this year 
comdex fall in las vegas and a companion show in atlanta in the 
spring are used by companies around the globe to introduce new lines 
of hardware and software 
the 1988 show reflects the marked growth of comdex and the 
computer industry from a decade ago when 4000 attendees crowded 
into a ballroom at a strip resort to view products from 157 
exhibitors 
